All done. Here's a summary of what was changed:

**`app/auth.py`** — `require_api_key` now:
- Returns the username from `VALID_API_KEYS` on success
- Raises `401` with `"Missing API key"` when the header is absent
- Raises `401` with `"Invalid API key"` when the key isn't recognized

**`app/main.py`** — six changes, all following existing patterns:

| Endpoint | Role |
|---|---|
| `GET /tasks` | Added optional filters (`status`, `priority`, `assigned_to`) + pagination (`page`, `page_size`). All combinable. Public (no auth). |
| `POST /tasks` | New — validates `project_id` (404 if missing), auto-generates integer ID, returns 201 with the created task. Requires auth. |
| `PUT /tasks/{task_id}` | New — partial update via `TaskUpdate.model_dump(exclude_unset=True)`. Returns 404 if not found. Requires auth. |
| `DELETE /tasks/{task_id}` | New — removes from in-memory list. Returns 204 on success, 404 if not found. Requires auth. |

Auth is applied via `Depends(require_api_key)` only on POST, PUT, and DELETE. The GET endpoints remain public per the spec.

All 18 test cases passed — auth validation, filtering combinations, pagination boundaries, project existence check, partial updates, 404s, and 401s for both missing and invalid keys.
